<SECOND>AM-Black Film Makers,0296</SECOND>
<HEAD>Spike Lee and Robert Townsend Honored as Independent Film Makers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PETER ALAN HARPER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Spike </PERSON> <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> and <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Townsend </PERSON>, the two major representatives of the newest wave of make-it-on-your-own black film makers, were honored Monday night for doing things their way. `` They are independent in spirit, they are determined and they fought against insurmountable odds and surmounted them,'' said <PERSON> Melvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Peebles </PERSON>, who overcame the odds a generation ago with `` Sweet Sweetback's Baadasssss Song.'' <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Peebles </PERSON>, an elder statesman of black film making, presented a special award to <PERSON> Townsend </PERSON> and <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> at the <ORGANIZATION> Black </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Filmmaker </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION>'s 10th anniversary gala and tribute at the Majestic Theater in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. The foundation is the nation's largest distributor of independently produced work by black film makers. Its 1,500 members include major film and television producers, writers, directors, actors and film students. Also being honored were films and videos produced independently of <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION> and commercial television in the last 10 years. <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> first became known three years ago for `` She's Got ta Have It,'' a sexual comedy about a young woman and her partners. He furthered his reputation with `` School Daze,'' a peek at black colleges, and his `` Do the Right Thing'' was the talk of the <LOCATION> Cannes </LOCATION> film festival last month. It premieres later this month. <PERSON> Townsend </PERSON> raised cash with his credit cards to finance `` Hollywood Shuffle,'' a revealing look at the stereotypes and prejudices black actors face on and off the screen in the movie-making world. He has moved on to four HBO specials and a feature film, `` The Mighty Quinn,'' with <PERSON> Oscar </PERSON> nominee <PERSON> Denzel </PERSON> <PERSON> Washington </PERSON>. <PERSON> Townsend </PERSON> now is writing and starring in a musical comedy, `` Heartbeats,'' about a singing group.
