PERSON> <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON>. In the absence of a single personality who can match <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON>'s religious and political authority, it seemed likely <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> would be ruled by a collective leadership <PERSON> Khamenei </PERSON> has endorsed the presidential candidacy of Parliament Speaker <PERSON> Hashemi </PERSON> <PERSON> Rafsanjani </PERSON>, 55, a political ally and the only declared candidate.
