ns to cross 250 yards of sand and rock and climb onto the bluff where the 172-acre military cemetery now stands as a memorial to those who fought and died. `` I do n't usually cry,'' <PERSON> Drodwill </PERSON> said. `` Maybe this trip will help soften the memory.''
