apart from putting out an official proposal in January as part of her State of the State message. `` She reminds me of groundhog day,'' said Sen. <PERSON> Leo </PERSON> <PERSON> Corbet </PERSON>. `` She came out and gave the State of the State, and saw her shadow and we have n't seen her since.'' No other governor in <LOCATION> Arizona </LOCATION>'s history has vetoed a full budget, according to the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> clerk's office. `` I think of all of the options the governor had available to her, she selected the worst one,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> majority leader <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Mawhinney </PERSON>. `` If the governor was unhappy with either the revenue package or the budget, then what we needed was clear indication of what it is that she felt she could n't live with,'' he added.
