ORGANIZATION> Ways </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Means </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, are calling for major changes, rather than repeal <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON>'s bill would delay the rules until January. It would view as non-discriminatory any plan that offered health insurance to 90 percent of all employees with the employer paying at least 60 percent of the premium. <PERSON> Rostenkowski </PERSON> earlier introduced a bill that, in essence, would accept any health plan that was available to 90 percent of rank-and-file workers for an employee premium not exceeding $ 10 a week for a single person or $ 20 for family coverage.
