' Earlier, official media carried these excerpts: `` I have done my duty, which is to give guidance. My hope is that you will listen to this advice, which will reach you after my death and is unstained by the desire for power, and save yourself from God's wrath. `` There should be no doubt that the Islamic revolution of <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> is separate from all other revolutions, in the quality of its struggle and in its motives. `` I have not said and I will not say that today, in this republic, the great Islam and all its aspects are being implemented and that ignorant and disorderly individuals are not committing acts against Islamic laws. `` But what I do say is that the legislative, judicial and executive branches are trying and will try to do a great deal to make the country Islamic.'' It is `` better to be wiped out honorably from the face of history by the hands of criminal Americans and Soviets ... than to have a super-comfortable life under the red flag of the East and the black flag of the West,'' <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON> declared. He said <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> had no greater source of pride `` than the fact that the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> with all its huge military arsenal and string of puppet regimes and the international mass media at its service, has been so disgraced and humbled against <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> that it does not know to whom it should resort.'' <PERSON> Khmomeini </PERSON> said <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> should guard against `` the conspiracies and plots of the enemies towards the <LOCATION> Islamic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Republic </LOCATION>. In the forefront of these is <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, this vile state terrorist, which has set fire to the whole world, and its ally the global Zionist -LRB- <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> -RRB-, which to attain its goals commits such crimes that pens are ashamed to document and tongues are ashamed to recite.'' Of <LOCATION> Iraqi </LOCATION> President <PERSON> Sad