fairly, but I certainly want them to treat him.'' Republicans on Tuesday circulated lapel buttons that said, `` Reform, not Revenge.'' `` What you have is the schoolyard bully who's afraid of getting punched back,'' said Rep. <PERSON> Barney </PERSON> <PERSON> Frank </PERSON>, D-Mass. The Republican political machine, under the leadership of <PERSON> Atwater </PERSON> at the <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Rollins </PERSON> at the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Congressional </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, has taken on a harder partisan edge and has plans to exploit the ethics issue. One <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> political source, who spoke only on condition of anonymity, said the campaign arm is sifting through Democrats' financial disclosure forms looking for mistakes they can capitalize on The Democrats are expected to select a replacement for <PERSON> Foley </PERSON> as majority leader next week. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Gephardt </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Missouri </LOCATION>, who ran unsuccessfully last year for the Democratic presidential nomination, is considered the favorite over <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> Jenkins </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Georgia </LOCATION>. The whip's race to replace <PERSON> Coelho </PERSON> is a contest among three already powerful <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Democrats: <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gray </PERSON> <PERSON> III </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION>, the chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Caucus </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Bonior </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION>, the chief deputy whip, and <PERSON> Beryl </PERSON> <PERSON> Anthon