<TEXT>
 WHERE WERE THE <LOCATION> WASHINGTON </LOCATION> WINES? <PERSON> Foley </PERSON> hosted a reception in his office for close friends and current and former staff after becoming speaker. Though <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> state produces some good white wine, the white wine was from <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 DEPARTING FROM THE TEXT: On only rare ocassions does <PERSON> Foley </PERSON> speak from a prepared text. His best speeches are usually from general talking points or are extemporaneous. <PERSON> Foley </PERSON> spent time during the morning working on his acceptance speech, but when he delivered it he followed it only in part. `` He followed it only vaguely,'' said one staffer.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 WHO IS THIS MAN? <PERSON> Foley </PERSON> was asked at his first formal news conference to introduce himself to the American public. `` I'm 60 years of age, 6-foot-4 and reportedly weigh 240 pounds, though I hope to make that less,'' he said.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 A DOG'S LIFE: <PERSON> Foley </PERSON>'s dog <PERSON> Alice </PERSON> has attracted a lot of attention over the past week, with some photographers more interested in taking pictures of her than the speaker. But <PERSON> Foley </PERSON> has bad news about her: `` <PERSON> Alice </PERSON> may not be with us much longer,'' he said. `` She's going on 17 years old, is totally deaf and it takes 12 hours of sleep to get her going in the morning.''
