<NOTE>LI SHOOTING</NOTE>
<TEXT>
 A young guard reportedly shot four times at Premier <PERSON> Li </PERSON> <PERSON> Peng </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION>'s Great Hall of the People on Sunday, slightly wounding him in the thigh. The guard was immediately killed, according to the report in a <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION> daily. Chinese sources said the man shot <PERSON> Li </PERSON> because a relative was killed by soldiers in Tiananmen Square.
