<HEAD>Paramount Launches $10.7 Billion Bid for Time</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES with comment from analyst, Paramount, ADDS background;
minor editing throughout. A version also moving on the financial wire.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SKIP WOLLENBERG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> late Tuesday announced a $ 10.7 billion takeover offer for publishing and cable giant <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which already plans a merger with <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. Paramount, an entertainment and communications company formerly known as <ORGANIZATION> Gulf </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Western </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, said it offered $ 175 a share for all of Time's stock The announcment came less than three weeks before Time and <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> shareholders are scheduled to vote on the merger agreement announced in March. The <ORGANIZATION> Time-Warner </ORGANIZATION> merger plan calls for a stock swap that the companies valued at $ 18 billion and said would create the world's largest media and entertainment company <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION> said its board would review the proposal and advised its shareholders not to do anything until they heard from the company. <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> officials had no immediate comment. Time, <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> and Paramount are all based in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. Time shares closed at $ 126 Tuesday in consolidated <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> trading, up $ 2.75. Paramount made its announcement after the market closed, and the company noted it was offering a price 60 percent higher than Time's share price just before the <ORGANIZATION> Time-Warner </ORGANIZATION> deal was announced There had been speculation for weeks that a bidder could emerge for Time despite its merger agreement with <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION>. But Time executives have privately insisted the company was not for sale. <PERSON> Harold </PERSON> <PERSON> Vogel </PERSON>, who follows the entertainment industry for <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, called it a `` fascinating situation.'' `` My feeling is that this is going to entail a much lengthier battle than Time and <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> had anticipated,'' <PERSON> Vogel </PERSON> said. `` Both companies were obviously in a rush to get this done as fast as possible for concern that someone could come in and upset the proposed merger.'' <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION>'s chairman and chief executive, said Time and <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> `` are a superb business fit.'' He said the acquisition of Time would represent `` the culmination of a six-year strategic transformation of our company into a leader in publishing and entertainment, a focus reflected by our new name.'' `` Together we will be the foremost American communications company, capable of competing on a global scale against foreign media giants,'' he said. Paramount announced in April that it intended to sell its consumer and commercial finance business, <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associates </ORGANIZATION>. It is expected the sale could produce $ 3 billion or more in revenue. <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> said <ORGANIZATION> Citibank </ORGANIZATION> has committed to provide $ 1 billion in financing for the offer and has said it is highly confident of its ability to arrange a syndicate of lenders to provide the rest. <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> said he told <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION>'s chairman and chief executive, <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Munro </PERSON>, that Paramount was willing to negotiate all aspects of its proposal. Paramount also said it would immediately withdraw its offer if Time shareholders approve the <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> transcation. Both <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION> shareholders are scheduled to vote on the proposed merger, a stock swap that the companies valued at $ 18 billion, on June 23. In a statement, <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION> said <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> advised <PERSON> Munro </PERSON> in a telelphone call Tuesday evening that `` Paramount was launching a hostile offer for Time's shares.'' Time said the offer was `` in contradiction to explicit assurances Mr. <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> had previously given Mr. <PERSON> Munro </PERSON>,'' but did not elaborate. Time has indicated that it has a $ 5 billion credit line available to begin its own offer for <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> or defend itself against a takeover. Paramount's entertainment interests include <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pictures </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Television </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Video </ORGANIZATION>. It owns Madison Square Garden and two professional sports teams: the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Knickerbockers </ORGANIZATION> in basketball and the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rangers </ORGANIZATION> in hockey. It also owns the <ORGANIZATION> MSG </ORGANIZATION> cable Network and a 50 percent interest in the <LOCATION> USA </LOCATION> cable network. In publishing, <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> owns <ORGANIZATION> Simon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZA