 Canal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> administrator named by Panamanian ruler <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> By law, the chief of government of <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> can nominate a new chief for the agency in January. That choice must be approved by the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> and by <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, and the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> served notice it would not go along with the Panamanian strongman. The 1989 federal fiscal year runs through Sept. 30.
