two weeks that the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> and other central banks are trying to get extra impact from their intervention by concealing it more than in the past. In <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, the dollar rose against the British pound. It cost $ 1.5665 to buy one pound, compared to $ 1.5815 late Monday. Later in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> the pound rose to $ 1.5710 from $ 1.5655 on Monday. In <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>, where trading ends before <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>'s business day begins, the dollar rosed 1.98 yen to a closing 142.63 yen. Later, in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, it was quoted at 143.28 yen. In <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> the dollar fell to 142.67 yen from 142.95. Other late dollar rates in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, compared with late Monday's rates, included: 1.9735 West German marks, down from 1.9855; 1.7095 Swiss francs, down from 1.7140; 1.2010 Canadian dollars, down from 1.2019; 6.7060 French francs, down from 6.7455; and 1,434 Italian lire, down from 1,442 Other late dollar rates in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>, compared with late Monday: 1.9850 West German marks, up from 1.9630; 1.7240 Swiss francs, up from 1.6950; 6.7360 French francs, up from 6.6645; 2.2370 Dutch guilders, up from 2.2010; 1,443.00 Italian lire, up from 1,416.50; 1.2015 Canadian dollars, up from 1.2003. In <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION>, gold fell $ 3.76 a troy ounce to close at a bid of $ 365.44. Gold fell in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> to a late bid price of $ 365.25 per troy ounce, compared with late Monday's $ 366.25. In <LOCATION> Zurich </LOCATION>, gold dropped to a bid of $ 365.30 compared with $ 366.00 late Monday. But on the Commodity Exchange in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, gold bullion for current delivery rose to $ 379.90 a troy ounce from $ 367.50 on Monday.